  "text": "Perhaps individuals with AUDs who are followed into their 60s might have demonstrated continued alcohol problems in their 40s and 50s but be most likely to survive into their 60s if they achieved Abstinence. The different rates of Abstinence might also relate to the current long follow-up period that gives additional opportunity for spontaneous remission that has been reported to occur in more than 20% of individuals with AUDs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
